                <h2>NOC Code Alignment: Why It Matters</h2>
                <p>
                    Your job offer's NOC code determines your eligibility, your SIRS score points, and which BC PNP streams you can apply through. <strong>The NOC code assigned to your position is not arbitrary</strong>‚Äîit must accurately reflect the actual duties of the job.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Officers compare your job offer duties against the official NOC code descriptions on the Statistics Canada website. If the duties listed in your offer do not substantially match the NOC code duties, the application may be refused or the NOC code may be reassigned.
                </p>

